<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_fæsm"
    xml:lang="os">
    <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>fæsm</orth></form>
    <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>fans</orth></form>
    <sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
            <q>шерсть осенней стрижки</q>
        </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
            <q>autumn shearing wool</q>
        </cit></sense>
    <re><form type="lemma"><orth>fæsmyn</orth></form><sense><sense><cit type="translation"
                    xml:lang="ru">
                    <q>из шерсти</q>
                </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                    <q>of wool</q>
                </cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                    <q>шерстяной</q>
                </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                    <q>woollen</q>
                </cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                    <q>сукно (домотканное, осетинское)</q>
                </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                    <q>broadcloth (homespun, Ossetic)</q>
                </cit></sense></sense></re>
    <cit type="exampleGroup">
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>tyn fæsmæj kænync, fīst næ bæzzy</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>сукно делают из шерсти осенней стрижки, шерсть весенней стрижки не годится</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>broadcloth is made from autumn shearing wool, spring shearing wool is no good</q>
            </cit>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <cit type="exampleGroup">
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>tyn fæsmæj kænync, fīst næ bæzzy</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>сукно делают из шерсти осенней стрижки, шерсть весенней стрижки не годится</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>broadcloth is made from autumn shearing wool, spring shearing wool is no good</q>
            </cit>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*paš-man-</w></mentioned>;
        заключает тот же корень, что %ifas-yn%i ‘чесать шерсть’. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>pašm</w><gloss><q>шерсть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="mnj"><lang/><w>pām, pōm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"
                ><lang/><w>pam</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"
            ><lang/><w>pām</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="oru"
                    ><lang/><w>pōm</w><gloss><q>шерсть овечья</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>pakš-man-</w><gloss><q>волосы, шерсть
            козули</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="goh"
                    ><lang/><w>fahs</w><gloss><q>хохол</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="grc"><lang/><w>πέκoς, πόκος</w><gloss><q>овечья
            шерсть</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="grc"
            ><w/><gloss><q>руно</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Остальное см. под <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_fasyn"/>. Дигорская форма %ifans%i — вторичная, ср. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_casm"/> | %icans%i ‘петля’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sasm"/> |
        %isans%i ‘клей’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_az"/> | %ianz%i ‘год’, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_fæzmyn"/> | %ifænzun%i ‘подражать’ (<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>361 прим., 379</biblScope></bibl>). Термины, связанные с шерстью и ее
        обработкой в осетинском, — иранского происхождения. Ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_q0yn"
                />.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Miller,_IF_21"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">стр.
                333</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">p. 333</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II 237</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">Traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
        ><lang/><w>*paš-man-</w></mentioned>; it has the same root as %ifas-yn%i ‘comb wool’. Cf.
            <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>pašm</w><gloss><q>wool</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/><w>pām, pōm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"
                ><lang/><w>pam</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"
            ><lang/><w>pām</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="oru"
                    ><lang/><w>pōm</w><gloss><q>sheep wool</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>pakš-man-</w><gloss><q>roe hair, roe
            wool</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="goh"
                    ><lang/><w>fahs</w><gloss><q>crest</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="grc"><lang/><w>πέκoς, πόκος</w><gloss><q>sheep
            wool</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="grc"
            ><w/><gloss><q>fleece</q></gloss></mentioned>, . See the rest under <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_fasyn"/>. The Digor form %ifans%i is secondary, cf. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_casm"/> | %icans%i ‘loop’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sasm"/> |
        %isans%i ‘glue’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_az"/> | %ianz%i ‘year’, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_fæzmyn"/> | %ifænzun%i ‘imitate’ (<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>361 footnote, 379</biblScope></bibl>). The terms associated with wool
        and its processing in Ossetic are of Iranian origin. Cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_q0yn"
                />.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Miller,_IF_21"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">стр.
                333</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">p. 333</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II 237</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
</entry>
